  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to investigate the development of partial pressure of carbon dioxide
      during the 6-min walking test and during night in Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease
      (COPD)-patients (GOLD stage IV). Therefore the partial pressure of carbon dioxide, oxygen
      saturation and the heart rate are registered by a device called &quot;Sentec&quot; during the mentioned
      periods. In addition a measurement of activity is realised by an activity monitor
      (&quot;Sensewear&quot;).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
